Linux and R
-----------
http://www.pitt.edu/~njc23/Linux_and_R.pdf
http://how-to.linuxcareer.com/introduction-to-gnu-r-on-linux-operating-system

* mount
* env | grep PATH; PATH="dir:$PATH"; echo $PATH;
* ls -1 | wc -l 
* whoami; sudo -u [usr]
* whoami; su - [usr]
* which R; type R; locate -b R | fgrep -w R/bin
* nohup ./[some.sh] &
* jobs; fg 1
